title: ‘Goose River Anthology’ is out
text:
‘Goose River Anthology’ is out Oct 23, 2015 
Waldoboro — Goose River Press has announced the publication of the 13th annual “Goose River Anthology,” featuring more than 90 talented writers from all parts of the country. 
“Goose River Anthology, 2015” follows in the footsteps of its predecessors as a fine collection of poetry, short stories, and essays from established and new writers. Books are available from the publisher, local bookstores or online. 
Goose River Press is currently accepting submissions for “Goose River Anthology, 2016” and full-length manuscripts; contact the publisher for submission guidelines. Authors may write to Goose River Press, 3400 Friendship Road, Waldoboro, ME 04572-6337; call 832-6665; email gooseriverpress@roadrunner.com; or visit gooseriverpress.com . 
Courier Publications’ A&E Editor Dagney C. Ernest can be reached at (207) 594-4401, ext. 115; or dernest@courierpublicationsllc.com.
